.SH git\-adr(1) \(en Architecture Decision Records management using git notes
.SS SYNOPSIS
\f[CR]git adr\f[R] OPTIONS COMMAND [ARGS]\&...
.SS DESCRIPTION
\f[B]git\-adr\f[R] is a command\-line tool for managing Architecture
Decision Records (ADRs) using git notes.
Unlike traditional file\-based ADR tools, git\-adr stores ADRs as git
notes attached to the repository, providing:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Rebase\-safe storage\f[R]: ADRs survive rebases and amends
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]No file conflicts\f[R]: ADRs don\(cqt clutter the working tree
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Distributed sync\f[R]: ADRs sync with
\f[CR]git fetch\f[R]/\f[CR]git push\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Commit linkage\f[R]: Connect decisions to implementation commits
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
