.SS COMMANDS
.SS Core Commands
.TP
\f[CR]git adr init\f[R]
Initialize ADR tracking in the current repository.
Sets up git notes namespace and configures remotes for ADR
synchronization.
.TP
\f[CR]git adr new\f[R] TITLE
Create a new Architecture Decision Record.
Opens your configured editor with a template for the ADR content.
.TP
\f[CR]git adr list\f[R] OPTIONS
List all Architecture Decision Records.
Supports filtering by status, tags, and date range.
.TP
\f[CR]git adr show\f[R] ADR_ID
Display a single ADR with rich formatting.
.TP
\f[CR]git adr edit\f[R] ADR_ID
Edit an existing ADR.
Supports quick metadata changes (\(enstatus, \(enadd\-tag) or full
editor mode.
.TP
\f[CR]git adr rm\f[R] ADR_ID [\(enforce]
Remove an ADR from git notes.
Use \(enforce to skip confirmation.
.TP
\f[CR]git adr search\f[R] QUERY
Search ADRs by content using full\-text search.
.SS Lifecycle Commands
.TP
\f[CR]git adr link\f[R] ADR_ID COMMIT
Associate an ADR with one or more commits, creating traceability between
decisions and their implementation.
.TP
\f[CR]git adr supersede\f[R] OLD_ADR_ID TITLE
Create a new ADR that supersedes an existing one.
The old ADR is automatically marked as superseded.
.SS Synchronization
.TP
\f[CR]git adr sync\f[R] [push|pull|both]
Synchronize ADR notes with a remote repository.
