.SS CONFIGURATION
git\-adr stores its configuration in git config.
Key settings include:
.TP
\f[CR]adr.namespace\f[R]
Git notes namespace for ADRs (default: \f[CR]adr\f[R])
.TP
\f[CR]adr.artifacts_namespace\f[R]
Git notes namespace for artifacts (default: \f[CR]adr\-artifacts\f[R])
.TP
\f[CR]adr.template\f[R]
Default template format: madr, nygard, y\-statement, alexandrian,
business, planguage
.TP
\f[CR]adr.editor\f[R]
Editor command for creating/editing ADRs
.TP
\f[CR]adr.artifact_warn_size\f[R]
Size threshold (bytes) for attachment warnings (default: 1048576)
.TP
\f[CR]adr.artifact_max_size\f[R]
Maximum attachment size in bytes (default: 10485760)
.TP
\f[CR]adr.sync.auto_push\f[R]
Auto\-push after modifications (default: false)
.TP
\f[CR]adr.sync.auto_pull\f[R]
Auto\-pull before reads (default: true)
.TP
\f[CR]adr.sync.merge_strategy\f[R]
Merge strategy: union, ours, theirs, cat_sort_uniq (default: union)
.TP
\f[CR]adr.ai.provider\f[R]
AI provider: openai, anthropic, google, bedrock, azure, ollama,
openrouter
.TP
\f[CR]adr.ai.model\f[R]
AI model name (provider\-specific)
.TP
\f[CR]adr.ai.temperature\f[R]
AI temperature 0.0\-1.0 (default: 0.7)
.TP
\f[CR]adr.wiki.platform\f[R]
Wiki platform: github, gitlab, auto
.TP
\f[CR]adr.wiki.auto_sync\f[R]
Auto\-sync to wiki after changes (default: false)
.PP
Use \f[CR]git adr config list\f[R] to see all settings.
