.IP
.EX
$ git adr list
.EE
.PP
List only accepted ADRs:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr list \-\-status accepted
.EE
.PP
Show a specific ADR:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr show 20250115\-use\-postgresql
.EE
.PP
Link an ADR to a commit:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr link 20250115\-use\-postgresql abc123
.EE
.PP
Search ADRs:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr search \(dqdatabase\(dq
.EE
.PP
Sync ADRs with remote:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr sync push
.EE
.SS TEMPLATE FORMATS
git\-adr supports multiple ADR template formats:
.TP
\f[B]madr\f[R] (Markdown Any Decision Records)
Full\-featured format with context, decision drivers, options, and
consequences.
.TP
\f[B]nygard\f[R] (Michael Nygard\(cqs original format)
Simple format with status, context, decision, and consequences.
.TP
\f[B]y\-statement\f[R]
Compact format using \(lqIn the context of\&...
we decided\&...\(rq structure.
.TP
\f[B]custom\f[R]
User\-defined templates in the repository.
